NtwsApInterfaceIndex.name: NtwsApInterfaceIndex
NtwsApInterfaceIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each AP network interface.

ntwsApIfTable.name: ntwsApIfTable
ntwsApIfTable.description: A table describing the network interfaces on all the APs currently present and managed by this AC (APs in ''ALIVE'' state).

ntwsApIfEntry.name: ntwsApIfEntry
ntwsApIfEntry.description: Information about a particular network interface on an AP attached to the AC.

ntwsApIfApSerialNum.name: ntwsApIfApSerialNum
ntwsApIfApSerialNum.description: The Serial Number of the AP containing this network interface.

ntwsApIfIndex.name: ntwsApIfIndex
ntwsApIfIndex.description: A unique value, greater than zero, for each AP network interface.

ntwsApIfName.name: ntwsApIfName
ntwsApIfName.description: The textual name of the interface.

ntwsApIfType.name: ntwsApIfType
ntwsApIfType.description: The type of AP network interfaces.

ntwsApIfMtu.name: ntwsApIfMtu
ntwsApIfMtu.description: The size of the largest packet which can be sent/received on the interface, specified in octets.

ntwsApIfHighSpeed.name: ntwsApIfHighSpeed
ntwsApIfHighSpeed.description: The nominal bandwidth of AP network interfaces in units of 1,000,000 bits per second.

ntwsApIfMac.name: ntwsApIfMac
ntwsApIfMac.description: The MAC address of this network interface.

ntwsApIfCompliance.name: ntwsApIfCompliance
ntwsApIfCompliance.description: The compliance statement for devices that implement AP If MIB. This compliance statement is for releases 7.1 and greater of AC (wireless switch) software.

ntwsApIfBasicGroup.name: ntwsApIfBasicGroup
ntwsApIfBasicGroup.description: Group of columnar objects implemented to provide basic Interface info in releases 7.1 and greater.
